'''Reverse architecture''' is a process of deducing the underlying architecture and design of a system by observing its behaviour.<ref>{{cite article| title=Experience with a reverse architecture approach to increase understanding | work=Proceedings of IEEE International Conference on Software Maintenance (ICSM '99) | date=1999 | publisher=[[IEEE]] | doi=10.1109/ICSM.1999.792596 | first1=A. | last1=von Mayrhauser | first2=J. | last2=Wang | first3=Q. | last3=Li }}</ref> It has its roots in the field of [[reverse engineering]].

Practicing reverse architecture is used to decipher the logistics of building. There are a variety of techniques available, the most notable being [[architecture driven modelling]].{{what|date=January 2018}}{{fact|date=January 2018}}

